    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Bug\r\n\r\nSetting a custom `concealcursor` value in an after/ftplugin does not \"stick\" when a buffer is loaded via bufadd + bufload. Other values from the ftplugin _are_ set correctly.\r\n\r\n- `nvim --version`: v0.5.0-773-g932585fd9 (edit: also v0.5.0-787-g98024853f)\r\n- Operating system/version: WSL/Ubuntu\r\n- Terminal name/version: alacritty\r\n- `$TERM`: xterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using `nvim -u NORC`\r\n\r\nSee https://github.com/taylan97/concealcursor-bug.vim for reproduction fixture and instructions.\r\n\r\n_This may not be a bug, it's unclear if loading a file via `bufadd -> bufload -> nvim_win_set_buf` is intended to load ftplugins or not. It definitely does apply some settings from the ftplugins file, so probably._\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\n`concealcursor `value is not correctly set from `after/ftplugin` file.\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\n`concealcursor `value should be set according to ftplugin.\r\n\r\nThank you for your time.",
