            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Yes perhaps. Though your inspections in that thread talk about `nvim_win_set_buf`'s behavior with *unloaded* buffers, while this buffer is loaded (via `bufload` at least, which to me (and the docs) certainly *implies* its being loaded).\r\n\r\nWhat's strangest about this issue is that some of the ftplugin settings *are* run (i.e. `showbreak`). So the file is obviously being executed, just perhaps in some sandbox/isolated state. \r\n\r\nI have tested it with both `set` and `setlocal` to the same result.\r\n\r\nIf I add `autocmd BufEnter * echo \"message\"` to `after/ftplugin/markdown.vim`, the message is echo'd out no matter the method of loading (\"b\" or \"n\").",
